The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, June 23: India?s forex reserves increased by $157 million to stand at $163.033 billion during the week ended June 16, against $162.876 billion during the week ended June 9. The reserves had decreased by $1.652 billion during the preceding week ended June 9 compared with a week ago. Foreign currency assets increased by $160 million to $155.247 billion during the seven-day period ended June 16, according to figures released by the Reserve Bank of India.

 Mumbai, June 23: SRF Ltd will buy back its shares through open market transactions at a price of up to Rs 250 per share. The company?s board has approved the buyback offer, which will remain open until June 22, 2007, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 New Delhi, June 23: Motorola will increase the headcount of its research and development division to take it to 4,000. The company has 3,500 engineers in its Bangalore and Hyderabad divisions.

 Calcutta, June 23: Oriental Bank of Commerce will make its foray into the life insurance business soon, chairman K.N. Prithviraj said. 

 g, June 23: Godrej will enter the Chinese market with fast moving consumer goods either through a joint venture or an acquisition.




